'''Dominik Livaković''' ({{IPA|hr|dôminik liʋǎːkoʋitɕ, domǐ-}};<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hjp.znanje.hr/index.php?show=search_by_id&id=f1ZhWhc%3D|title=Dȍminik|quote=Dȍminik (Domìnik)|work=Hrvatski Jezični portal|access-date=17 March 2018|language=sh}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://hjp.znanje.hr/index.php?show=search_by_id&id=e19uWxc%3D&keyword=lijevi|title=lijȇvī|quote=Liváković|work=Hrvatski Jezični portal|access-date=17 March 2018|language=sh}}</ref> born 9 January 1995) is a Croatian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Croatian Football League]] club [[GNK Dinamo Zagreb|Dinamo Zagreb]], on loan from [[Süper Lig]] club [[Fenerbahçe S.K. (football)|Fenerbahçe]], and the [[Croatia national football team|Croatia national team]].

==Club career==
===NK Zagreb===
Livaković became part of [[NK Zagreb]]'s first team at the beginning of the [[2012–13 Croatian First Football League|2012–13 season]]. Initially the club's second-choice goalkeeper, he made his league debut on 31 August 2012, playing the full match in a 1–0 defeat at home to [[HNK Cibalia]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Zagreb vs Cibalia|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2012/08/31/croatia/1-hnl/nk-zagreb/hnk-cibalia-vinkovci/1287280/|publisher=Soccerway|access-date=29 September 2014}}</ref> He soon became the club's number one and made a total of 104 league appearances over four seasons, including 90 in the [[Prva HNL]].

===Dinamo Zagreb===
On 30 August 2015, he agreed to join [[GNK Dinamo Zagreb|Dinamo Zagreb]] at the beginning of the [[2016–17 GNK Dinamo Zagreb season|2016–17 season]]. He made his league debut for the club on 2 October 2016 in a goalless draw at home to [[HNK Hajduk Split|Hajduk Split]]. On 18 October 2016, he made his first appearance in the [[UEFA Champions League]] in a 1–0 defeat at home to [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/uefa-champions-league/articles/dinamo-zagreb-0-1-sevilla-sampaolis-men-recor |title=Dinamo Zagreb 0-1 Sevilla: Sampaoli's Men Record Second Consecutive Away Win |publisher=beIN SPORTS |date=18 October 2016 }}</ref>

On 30 July 2019, in a [[2019–20 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] [[2019–20 UEFA Champions League qualifying phase and play-off round#Second qualifying round|qualifying]] 3–0 victory over [[FC Saburtalo Tbilisi|Saburtalo Tbilisi]], Livaković broke [[Dražen Ladić]]'s record for most minutes from the start of Dinamo's season without conceding a goal (413), set in [[1995–96 Croatian First Football League|1995]].<ref>{{Cite web|date=30 July 2019|title=Livaković postao novi klupski rekorder|url=https://gnkdinamo.hr/hr/Novosti/Clanak/livakovic-postao-novi-klupski-rekorder|access-date=6 September 2020|website=GNK Dinamo|language=hr-HR}}</ref> He conceded his first goal of the [[2019–20 GNK Dinamo Zagreb season|season]] three days later, in a 3–1 [[2019–20 Croatian First Football League|league]] victory over [[HNK Gorica|Gorica]], set the new record at 535.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Hina|date=2 August 2019|title=Dinamo slomio Goricu: Olmo zabio i asistirao, Lovrić matirao Livakovića|url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/rubrika/nogomet/dinamo-slomio-goricu-olmo-zabio-i-asistirao---570406.html|access-date=6 September 2020|website=Gol.hr|language=hr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=2 August 2019|title=Dinamo Zagreb 2019-20 - Forum - Sportnet.hr|url=https://sportnet.rtl.hr/sportnetklub/nogomet-1/dinamo-zagreb-2019-20-358600/p5836154/#poruka5836154|access-date=6 September 2020|website=sportnet.rtl.hr|language=hr|archive-date=7 July 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230707124437/https://sportnet.hr/sportnetklub/nogomet-1/dinamo-zagreb-2019-20-358600/p5836154/#poruka5836154|url-status=dead}}</ref>

On 26 August 2020, in a [[2020–21 UEFA Champions League qualifying phase and play-off round#Second qualifying round|Champions League qualifier]] against [[CFR Cluj]], Livaković saved [[Ciprian Deac]]'s [[Penalty kick (association football)|penalty kick]]. The game went to [[Overtime (sports)#Association football|extra time]] and ended as a 2–2 draw, resulting in a [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shoot-out]]. Livaković saved [[Cătălin Golofca]]'s attempt which would turn out crucial as Dinamo won the shootout 6–5 and progressed to the [[2020–21 UEFA Champions League qualifying phase and play-off round#Third qualifying round|third qualifying round]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=Ničota|first=Tomo|date=26 August 2020|title=Dinamovci s igračem manje izborili 3. pretkolo! Primili gol u nadoknadi, pa prošli na penale|url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/liga-prvaka/dinamovci-s-igracem-manje-izborili-3-pretkolo-primili-gol-u-nadoknadi-pa-prosli-na-penale-15015594|access-date=27 August 2020|website=Sportske novosti|language=hr-hr}}</ref> In the [[2020–21 UEFA Europa League|2020–21 Europa League]] [[2020–21 UEFA Europa League group stage#Group K|group stage]], Livaković was praised for his performances after he conceded only one goal in five games and led Dinamo to the first place in their group.<ref>{{Cite web|date=11 December 2020|title=Livaković zaprepastio nogometne fanove: "Najbolji je vratar svijeta. Zapamtite to ime"|url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/rubrika/nogomet/dominik-livakovic-odusevio-nogometne-fanove-dvostrukom-obranom---631735.html|access-date=12 December 2020|website=Gol.hr|language=hr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=N. Z. L.|date=11 December 2020|title=FUDBALSKA EVROPA U NEVERICI ZBOG OVOG POTEZA Golman Dinama od sinoć ima novi nadimak zbog ove ČUDESNE INTERVENCIJE! /VIDEO/|url=https://sport.blic.rs/fudbal/evropski-fudbal/dominik-livakovic-golman-cudesna-odbrana-hobotnica-fk-dinamo-zagreb-video-liga-evrope/v2vh04e|access-date=12 December 2020|website=Blic|language=sr}}</ref> He notably saved [[Steven Berghuis]]'s penalty kick in Dinamo's 0–0 draw with [[Feyenoord]] on 22 October.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Ničota|first=Tomo|date=4 December 2020|title=Pet ključnih Dinamovih točaka na putu do europskog proljeća, sve je krenulo s Livakovićevim potezom|url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/europska-liga/pet-kljucnih-dinamovih-tocaka-na-putu-do-europskog-proljeca-sve-je-krenulo-s-livakovicevim-potezom-15034993|access-date=12 December 2020|website=Sportske novosti|language=hr-hr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Tolić|first=Josip|date=22 October 2020|title=Livi, majstore! Pogledajte kako je skinuo četvrti penal u sezoni|url=https://www.24sata.hr/sport/livi-majstore-pogledajte-kako-je-skinuo-cetvrti-penal-u-sezoni-723706|access-date=12 December 2020|website=24sata|language=hr}}</ref> On 18 March 2021, in the [[2020–21 UEFA Europa League knockout phase#Round of 16|Europa League Round of 16]] against [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]], Livaković saved [[Harry Kane]]'s close-range effort when the score was 3–0 for Dinamo, leading the club to a 3–2 [[Aggregate Score|aggregate]] victory and the first [[UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] [[2020–21 UEFA Europa League knockout phase#Quarter-finals|quarter-final]] in its history.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Olivari|first=Davorin|date=15 April 2021|title=Evo kako bi trebao izgledati Dinamo u lovu na povijest! Kapetan Ademi je spreman, genijalac u sredini...|url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/europska-liga/evo-kako-bi-trebao-izgledati-dinamo-u-lovu-na-povijest-kapetan-ademi-je-spreman-genijalac-u-sredini-15065519|url-status=live|access-date=15 April 2021|website=Sportske novosti|language=hr-hr|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210415063506/https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/europska-liga/evo-kako-bi-trebao-izgledati-dinamo-u-lovu-na-povijest-kapetan-ademi-je-spreman-genijalac-u-sredini-15065519 |archive-date=15 April 2021 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=A. Čaušević|date=18 March 2021|title=Odbrana vrijednija od gola: Nestvarno šta je Livaković odbranio Kaneu!|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/dominik-livakovic-odbrana-tottenham-harry-kane/394146|url-status=live|access-date=15 April 2021|newspaper=Sportsport|language=bs|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210415063508/https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/dominik-livakovic-odbrana-tottenham-harry-kane/394146 |archive-date=15 April 2021 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=18 March 2021|title=Obrana o kojoj će se dugo pričati: Livaković je sjajnom paradom u produžetku spasio Dinamo|url=https://telesport.telegram.hr/na-prvu/obrana-o-kojoj-ce-se-dugo-pricati-livakovic-je-sjajnom-paradom-u-produzetku-spasio-dinamo/|url-status=live|access-date=15 April 2021|website=Telesport|language=hr|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210415063518/https://telesport.telegram.hr/na-prvu/obrana-o-kojoj-ce-se-dugo-pricati-livakovic-je-sjajnom-paradom-u-produzetku-spasio-dinamo/ |archive-date=15 April 2021 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=18 March 2021|title=Mourinho's sorry Spurs dumped out by Orsic hat-trick|url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/international-football/dinamo-zagreb-vs-tottenham-h/cronica/2021/03/18/6053bc0022601d584f8b45e4.html|url-status=live|access-date=15 April 2021|website=Marca|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210319000424/https://www.marca.com/en/football/international-football/dinamo-zagreb-vs-tottenham-h/cronica/2021/03/18/6053bc0022601d584f8b45e4.html |archive-date=19 March 2021 }}</ref>

===Fenerbahçe===
[[File:Dominik Livaković Karşılama, Fenerbahçe - FC Twente 24082023.webm|thumb|Dominik Livaković's welcoming ceremony before the Fenerbahçe v. [[FC Twente|Twente]] [[2023–24 UEFA Europa Conference League|UEFA Europa Conference League]] [[2023–24 UEFA Europa Conference League qualifying phase and play-off round (Main Path)#PO 10.1|play-off first round game]].]]
[[File:Dominik Livaković, Fenerbahçe v. Ankaragücü.jpg|thumb|Dominik Livaković, Fenerbahçe v. [[MKE Ankaragücü|Ankaragücü]] (28 January 2024)]]
On 25 August 2023, Livaković joined [[Süper Lig]] club [[Fenerbahçe S.K. (football)|Fenerbahçe]] on a €6.65 million fee, signing a 5-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ailemize hoş geldin Dominik Livakovic |trans-title=Welcome to our family Dominik Livakovic |language=tr |url=https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2023/8/ailemize-hos-geldin-dominik-livakovic |date=25 August 2023 |access-date=25 August 2023 |publisher=[[Fenerbahçe S.K.]]}}</ref> On 6 September, he was announced as one of the nominees for the [[2023 Ballon d'Or#Yashin Trophy|2023 Yashin Trophy]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/France-Football/Actualites/Trophee-yachine-2023-la-liste-complete-des-nommes/1418229 |title=Trophée Yachine 2023 : la liste complète des nommés |language=fr |website=[[L'Équipe]] |date=6 September 2023 |accessdate=6 September 2023}}</ref>

On 17 September 2023, he made his [[Süper Lig]] debut against [[Antalyaspor]] in a 3–2 home win in [[Şükrü Saraçoğlu Stadium]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Fenerbahçe 3-2 Bitexen Antalyaspor |language=tr |url=https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2023/9/fenerbahce-3-2-bitexen-antalyaspor |date=17 September 2023 |access-date=21 January 2025 |publisher=[[Fenerbahçe S.K.]]}}</ref> On 21 September 2023, he made his continental debut with the team against [[FC Nordsjaelland|Nordsjaelland]] in a 3–1 win, [[UEFA Conference League]] home match.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Fenerbahçe 3-1 Nordsjaelland |language=tr |url=https://www.fenerbahce.org/news/futbol/2023/9/fenerbahce-3-1-nordsjaelland |date=21 September 2023 |access-date=21 January 2025 |publisher=[[Fenerbahçe S.K.]]}}</ref>

On 26 September 2024, he saved his compatriot [[Franjo Ivanović]]'s 90+2 minutes penalty kick against [[Royale Union Saint-Gilloise|Union Saint-Gilloise]] in a 2–1 win, [[UEFA Europa League]] home match.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Fenerbahçe 2-1 Union SG |language=tr |url=https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2024/9/fenerbahce-2-1-union-sg |date=26 September 2024 |access-date=21 January 2025 |publisher=[[Fenerbahçe S.K.]]}}</ref>

==== Loan to Girona ====
On 1 September 2025, Livaković joined [[La Liga]] club [[Girona FC|Girona]] on loan for the remainder of the 2025–26 season.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Transfer Bilgilendirme |url=https://fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2025/9/transfer-bilgilendirme-tr |date= 2025-09-01 |access-date=2025-09-01 |website=www.Fenerbahçe SK |language=tr}}</ref> However, Girona's coach [[Míchel (footballer, born 1975)|Míchel]] later publicly criticized Livaković's commitment to the club, stating that he refused to play in the [[2025–26 Copa del Rey|Copa del Rey]] against [[Ourense CF]] in place of the fever-ridden goalkeeper [[Paulo Gazzaniga]], as he was aiming to join another team, having already featured for Fenerbahçe earlier in the season, and focus on preparing for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup|World Cup]]. As a result, Míchel confirmed that Livaković would not feature for the team.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/articles/girona-coach-says-goalkeeper-livakovic-170248263.html |title=Girona coach says goalkeeper Livakovic won't play for the team again |publisher=Yahoo Sports |date=11 December 2025 }}</ref>

==== Return to Dinamo Zagreb ====
On 30 January 2026, Livaković rejoined his former club Dinamo Zagreb on loan.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://gnkdinamo.hr/hr/vijesti/clanak/dominik-livakovic-ponovno-u-dinamu |title=Dominik Livaković ponovno u Dinamu |publisher=GNK Dinamo Zagreb |language=hr |date=30 January 2026 }}</ref>

==International career==
Livaković received his first call-up to the [[Croatia national football team]] for their [[Exhibition match#International career|friendly match]] against [[Moldova national football team|Moldova]] in May 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Croatia v Moldova|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/croatia-vs-moldova/teams/354998|website=[[Sky Sports]]|date=27 May 2016|access-date=10 June 2016}}</ref> He debuted against [[Chile national football team|Chile]] in the [[2017 China Cup]] where Croatia lost on penalties.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Zdravko|last=Barišić|title=Livaković: Upoznao sam Turčina koji nam je zabio 2008. Zbog njega sam povraćao dva dana|url=https://www.24sata.hr/sport/livakovic-upoznao-sam-turcina-koji-nam-je-zabio-2008-zbog-njega-sam-povracao-dva-dana-980923|website=[[24sata (Croatia)|24sata Croatia]]|date=6 May 2024|language=hr}}</ref>

In May 2018 Livaković was named to Croatia's preliminary 32-man squad for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in Russia, and was eventually part of the [[2018 FIFA World Cup squads#Croatia|team]] that finished runners-up after losing the [[2018 FIFA World Cup Final|final]] against [[France national football team|France]].<ref>{{cite web| url = https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/revealed-every-world-cup-2018-squad-23-man-preliminary-lists/oa0atsduflsv1nsf6oqk576rb| title = Revealed: Every World Cup 2018 squad - Final 23-man lists|website=[[Goal (website)|Goal]]}}</ref> He made his competitive debut against [[England national football team|England]] in the [[2018–19 UEFA Nations League A|2018–19 Nations League]] match held on 12 October 2018 at [[Stadion Rujevica]] in [[Rijeka]], which ended in a goalless draw.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Hrvoje|last=Tironi|title=Livaković se ne boji Engleza: Već sam skidao Kaneu zicere|url=https://www.24sata.hr/sport/livakovic-se-ne-boji-engleza-vec-sam-skidao-kaneu-zicere-594715|website=24sata Croatia|date=12 October 2018|language=hr}}</ref>

On 5 December 2022, in the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] [[2022 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Japan vs Croatia|round of 16]] match against [[Japan national football team|Japan]], Livaković was named [[Man of the Match]] after saving three [[Penalty kick (association football)|penalties]] in the [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|shoot-out]] to help his side advance to the [[2022 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Croatia vs Brazil|quarter-finals]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Japan-Croatia |url=https://www.fifa.com/fifaplus/en/match-centre/match/17/255711/285073/400128132 |website=FIFA.com |access-date=5 December 2022 |date=5 December 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=HNS on Twitter |url=https://twitter.com/HNS_CFF/status/1599827122901557248 |website=Twitter |publisher=Croatian Football Federation |access-date=5 December 2022 |date=5 December 2022}}</ref>{{Better source needed|date=May 2024}} In said quarter-finals, he saved another penalty in the shoot-out against [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]], helping Croatia advance to the [[2022 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Argentina vs Croatia|semi-finals]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Livakovic saves three penalties as Croatia advances. He also saved one penalty against Brazil while another was missed in the quarterfinals to send his team to the semifinals.|url=https://www.beinsports.com/au/2022-fifa-world-cup/video/livakovic-saves-three-penalties-as-croatia-ad/2000147 |website=[[BeIN Sports]]|access-date=5 December 2022 |date=5 December 2022}}</ref> He produced eleven saves, with the performance earning him another Man of the Match award, as well as the rare 10/10 rating from ''[[L'Équipe]]'', making him the 15th player in the magazine's history to be awarded it.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.index.hr/mobile/sport/clanak/livakovicu-desetka-lequipea-brazilcima-se-povraca-od-golmana-zagrebackog-dinama/2419564.aspx |title=Livakoviću desetka L'Equipea. "Brazilcima se povraća od golmana zagrebačkog Dinama" |website=[[Index.hr]] |date=10 December 2022 |access-date=10 December 2022 |language=hr}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Article/Les-notes-de-croatie-bresil-livakovic-sur-un-nuage/1369281 |title=Les notes de Croatie-Brésil : Livakovic sur un nuage |website=[[L'Équipe]] |date=9 December 2022 |access-date=10 December 2022 |language=fr}}</ref> Despite being one of the favorites for the [[FIFA World Cup Golden Glove|Golden Glove]] award,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.24sata.hr/sport/osim-bronce-jedan-ce-vatreni-u-subotu-loviti-prestizni-trofej-879583 |title=Osim bronce, jedan će 'vatreni' u subotu loviti prestižni trofej |first=Josip |last=Tolić |date=14 December 2022 |access-date=23 December 2022 |website=[[24sata (Croatia)|24sata]] |language=hr}}</ref> he lost it to [[Emiliano Martínez]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.telegraf.rs/sport/katar-2022/3602887-najveca-polemika-posle-mundijala-livakovic-ili-martinez |title=Najveća polemika posle Mundijala: Nepravda naneta Livakoviću, Martinezu počasti sa skoro 4 puta manje odbrana |website=Telegraf|date=19 December 2022 |access-date=23 December 2022 |language=sr}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://n1info.hr/sport-klub/nogomet/livakovic-zlatna-rukavica-ovo-je-najveca-nagrada/ |title=Livaković: "Zlatna rukavica? Ovo je najveća nagrada" |date=19 December 2022 |access-date=23 December 2022 |website=[[N1 (TV channel)|N1 Hrvatska]] |language=hr}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/rubrika/nogomet/vrijednost-trojice-vatrenih-znatno-skocila-nakon-katra-pogledajte-na-koliko-su-procijenjeni---758124.html |title=Vrijednost trojice Vatrenih znatno skočila nakon Katra, pogledajte na koliko su procijenjeni|website=[[Gol.hr]]|date=23 December 2022|language=hr}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Livaković hails from a prominent family. His father Zdravko Livaković is a [[Construction engineering|construction engineer]] and a former State Secretary in the [[Ministry of the Sea, Transport and Infrastructure (Croatia)|Ministry of the Sea, Transport and Infrastructure]] during the mandate of [[Božidar Kalmeta]]. His paternal grandfather and grandmother were a [[radiologist]] and an English teacher, respectively.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |last=Mikuličin |first=Ivana |date=29 July 2018 |title=DOMINIK LIVAKOVIĆ 'U mojoj obitelji svi su doktori i inženjeri, no ja sam od malena znao čime ću se baviti...' |url=https://www.jutarnji.hr/scena/domace-zvijezde/dominik-livakovic-u-mojoj-obitelji-svi-su-doktori-i-inzenjeri-no-ja-sam-od-malena-znao-cime-cu-se-baviti-7659474 |access-date=18 June 2022 |website=[[Jutarnji list]] |language=hr-hr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Puljić-Šego |first=Iva |date=4 November 2009 |title=Livaković: Glavna je zvijezda lupeški sindikalac koji ne dolazi na posao |url=https://www.vecernji.hr/vijesti/livakovic-glavna-je-zvijezda-lupeski-sindikalac-koji-ne-dolazi-na-posao-45365 |access-date=18 June 2022 |website=[[Večernji list]] |language=hr}}</ref> His mother Manuela Skoblar is [[Josip Skoblar]]'s first cousin once removed.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Tironi |first=Hrvoje |date=6 March 2019 |title=Moj dida i ja: Svemu me naučio, on je najzaslužniji za sve ovo... |url=https://www.24sata.hr/sport/moj-dida-i-ja-svemu-me-naucio-on-je-najzasluzniji-za-sve-ovo-617610 |access-date=18 June 2022 |website=[[24sata (Croatia)|24sata]] |language=hr}}</ref>

In June 2022, Livaković married his long-time girlfriend Helena Matić in the [[Zadar Cathedral]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Banjeglav Perković |first=Gorana |date=18 June 2022 |title=Dominik Livaković i Helena Matić izgovorili sudbonosno da! Hrvatska Meghan Markle izgledala je poput princeze |url=https://www.gloria.hr/gl/fokus/price/dominik-livakovic-i-helena-matic-izgovorili-sudbonosno-da-hrvatska-meghan-markle-izgledala-je-poput-princeze-15212140 |access-date=18 June 2022 |website=[[Gloria (magazine)|Gloria]] |language=hr-hr}}</ref>

He credited [[Danijel Subašić]], [[David de Gea]], and [[Iker Casillas]] as his football role models.<ref name=":0" />

